berkeley-db-4.8.30.NC: rename __atomic_compare_exchange (compilation patch).

Needed only by the FULL GUI build path that uses Berkeley DB (the IRC 0.1.0/0.1.3
clients, and the "purist" full-rebuild variant). The cli-rebuild and the default
full-rebuild use a flat-file DB and do NOT need this.

Berkeley DB 4.8 (2010) defines a static inline named __atomic_compare_exchange.
On GCC 4.4+ that identifier became a compiler built-in, so the build fails with a
clash. Rename DB's function (and the macro that calls it) to a private name.

This is a COMPILATION patch (modern-toolchain fix), not a change to Satoshi's
code. Apply inside the db-4.8.30.NC source tree:
    patch -p1 < berkeley-db-4.8-gcc-atomic.patch

--- a/dbinc/atomic.h
+++ b/dbinc/atomic.h
@@ -144,7 +144,7 @@
 #define	atomic_inc(env, p)	__atomic_inc(p)
 #define	atomic_dec(env, p)	__atomic_dec(p)
 #define	atomic_compare_exchange(env, p, o, n)	\
-	__atomic_compare_exchange((p), (o), (n))
+	__atomic_compare_exchange_db((p), (o), (n))
 static inline int __atomic_inc(db_atomic_t *p)
 {
 	int	temp;
@@ -176,7 +176,7 @@
  * http://gcc.gnu.org/onlinedocs/gcc-4.1.0/gcc/Atomic-Builtins.html
  * which configure could be changed to use.
  */
-static inline int __atomic_compare_exchange(
+static inline int __atomic_compare_exchange_db(
 	db_atomic_t *p, atomic_value_t oldval, atomic_value_t newval)
 {
 	atomic_value_t was;
